{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"agent_message","text":"I have enough context to map the change. I’m treating this as three coupled pieces so the repo ends up with one actual entrypoint instead of loose helpers:\n\n1. Add a typed, library-owned stimulus registry with canonical family IDs, discoverable presets, family/name aliases, default timing/spatial/luminance blocks, and strict override validation.\n2. Add a normalization API that accepts YAML/manifest-style mappings and resolves them into one normalized spec plus registry metadata, including the Milestone 1 `moving_edge` compatibility path.\n3. Wire in regression coverage around happy paths and failure modes, then run the repo test suite, stage the ticket changes, and create the requested commit."}}
